<p>
<p>It is given that P(A) = 0.4, P(B) = 0.25 and P(A ∩ B) = 0.1. Are the events A and B independent?</p>
</p>]]></text>
</questiontext>
<generalfeedback format="html">
<text><![CDATA[<p>
</p>]]></text>
</generalfeedback>
<penalty>0</penalty>
<defaultgrade>1</defaultgrade>
<shuffleanswers>false</shuffleanswers>
<single>true</single>
<answernumbering>abc</answernumbering>
<answer fraction="0" format="html">
<text><![CDATA[<p>
Yes, because P(A) = P(B | A).
</p>]]></text>
<feedback format="html">
<text><![CDATA[<p>
Yes, because P(A) = P(B | A)…: Incorrect
</p>]]></text>
</feedback>
</answer>
<answer fraction="100" format="html">
<text><![CDATA[<p>
Yes, because P(A) x P(B) = P(A ∩ B).
</p>]]></text>
<feedback format="html">
<text><![CDATA[<p>
Yes, because P(A) x P(B) = P(A ∩ B)…: Correct
</p>]]></text>
</feedback>
</answer>
<answer fraction="0" format="html">
<text><![CDATA[<p>
No, because P(A) ≠ P(A | B).
</p>]]></text>
<feedback format="html">
<text><![CDATA[<p>
No, because P(A) ≠ P(A | B)…: Incorrect
</p>]]></text>
</feedback>
</answer>
<answer fraction="0" format="html">
<text><![CDATA[<p>
No, because P(A ∩ B) ≤ P(A).
</p>]]></text>
<feedback format="html">
<text><![CDATA[<p>
No, because P(A ∩ B) ≤ P(A)…: Incorrect
</p>]]></text>
</feedback>
</answer>
